---
layout: null
sitemap: false
---
{%- comment -%}
Build-time page manifest — the repo path of every markdown page, as a flat JSON
array. The lab repo is private, so the GitHub Contents API 404s for anonymous
visitors; .folder / .sitemap read this static file (served from the public Pages
site) to enumerate a folder with no API call. One SSOT: Jekyll already knows
every page at build, so this is generated, never hand-kept. layout:null so the
default HTML layout does not wrap the JSON.
{%- endcomment -%}
[
{%- assign mds = site.pages | where_exp: "p", "p.name contains '.md'" -%}
{%- for p in mds -%}
"docs/{{ p.path }}"{%- unless forloop.last -%},{%- endunless -%}
{%- endfor -%}
]
